* Can you write a simple emacs lisp function that has 1 optional argument? If the argument is passed in, return the argument. If the argument is not passed in, return some hardcoded  value.

* - Emacs Lisp function with optional argument

#+BEGIN_SRC emacs-lisp
(defun my-simple-func (&optional arg)
  "Return ARG if provided, else return 'default-value."
  (if arg
      arg
    'default-value))
#+END_SRC

- Usage examples
- (my-simple-func 42) ⇒ 42
- (my-simple-func)    ⇒ default-value

* * 